<article>
    <h1>Clessidra</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210103/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-03"><time>2021-01-03</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Where: 01-05 Down­town Gallery, 6A Shen­ton Way; open: 10.30am to 6pm (week­days), 10am to 4pm (Satur­days), closed on Sun­days Info: www.clessidra.com.sg</p>
    <p>In­dulge in pre­mium Ital­ian prod­ucts from Clessidra, a gourmet bou­tique that show­cases pro­duce sourced from Italy by hus­ban­dand-wife team Francesco Pas­quetti and Emanuela Cat­ta­neo.</p>
    <p>Al­though the brand was founded in 2011, its phys­i­cal store in the Cen­tral Busi­ness Dis­trict was started only early last year.</p>
    <p>Pop­u­lar op­tions i nclude I &P ex­tra vir­gin olive oil (from $28), pro­duced in Italy’s Canino coun­try­side; and pasta by Mulino Val d’Or­cia (from $14), made from stone-milled flour and an­cient grains such as Se­na­tore Cap­pelli du­rum wheat and Verna soft wheat.</p>
    <p>Pair the pasta with Pi­etraSanta Po­modoro Fi­aschetto pulped to­mato sauce ($20 for 500g), which is made with sweet and juicy toma­toes.</p>
    <p>You can also get pantry sets or ham­pers for gift­ing.</p>
    <p>Mr Pas­quetti says: “Our pro­ducer-part­ners are of­ten off the trod­den path and are lit­tle gems that are sel­dom seen out of Italy. These pro­duc­ers, which are of­ten fam­ily-run, cre­ate their food the tra­di­tional way.”</p>

